New York: Houghton, Mifflin & Company, pp.&nbsp;133\u2013155.\n* [[\u00c9douard Rod|Rod, \u00c9douard]] (1892). [https://archive.org/stream/lesidesmorales00rodeuoft#page/262/mode/2up \"Le Vicomte E.M. de Vog\u00fc\u00e9.\"] In: ''Les Id\u00e9es Morales du Temps Pr\u00e9sent.'' Paris: Perrin, pp.&nbsp;263\u2013289.\n* [[Ernest Seilli\u00e8re|Seilli\u00e8re, Ernest]] (1938). \"Eug\u00e8ne Melchior de Vog\u00fce et les Probl\u00e8mes Sociaux du Temps Pr\u00e9sent.\" In: ''Le Naturalisme de Montaigne et Autres Essais.'' Paris: \u00c9ditions de la Nouvelle Revue Critique, pp.&nbsp;135\u2013182.\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{commons category|Eug\u00e8ne-Melchior de Vog\u00fc\u00e9}}\n* [http://catalog.hathitrust.org/Search/Home?lookfor=%22Vog%C3%BC%C3%A9,%20Eug%C3%A8ne-Melchior,%20vicomte%20de,%201848-1910%22&type=author&inst= Works by Eug\u00e8ne-Melchior de Vog\u00fc\u00e9], at [[Hathi Trust]]\n*[http://www.academie-francaise.fr/les-immortels/eugene-melchior-de-vogue?fauteuil=39&election=22-11-1888 Academie Francaise Biography]\n*[http://fortnightlyreview.co.uk/2010/05/dostoyevski-and-the-religion-of-suffering-part-i/ \"Dostoyevsky and the Religion of Suffering\"], from ''Le Roman Russe''.\n\n{{Acad\u00e9mie fran\u00e7aise Seat 39}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vogue, Melchior De}}\n[[Category:1848 births]]\n[[Category:1910 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Nice]]\n[[Category:Counts of Vog\u00fc\u00e9|Melchior de Vogue]]\n[[Category:Marquesses of Vog\u00fc\u00e9|Melchior de Vogue]]\n[[Category:French archaeologists]]\n[[Category:19th-century French diplomats]]\n[[Category:French essayists]]\n[[Category:19th-century French journalists]]\n[[Category:French literary critics]]\n[[Category:French philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Politicians of the French Third Republic]]\n[[Category:French travel writers]]\n[[Category:Viscounts of France]]\n[[Category:Members of the Acad\u00e9mie fran\u00e7aise]]\n[[Category:Corresponding Members of the St Petersburg Acade